---
title: Pagliacci Salad
tags: salad
servings: 4-6
---

For the dressing, combine @garlic cloves{2}, @red wine vinegar{2%tbsp}, @egg{1} (whole), @egg yolk{1}, @lemon juice{2%tbsp}, @Dijon mustard{1%tbsp}, @Worcestershire sauce{1%tsp}, @fresh or dried tarragon{1%tbsp}, @salt{1%tsp}, @black pepper{1/2%tsp}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp} in a blender and blitz until well combined. With the blender running on high, slowly drizzle in @extra virgin olive oil{2/3%cup} to emulsify.

Combine @chopped green leaf lettuce{1%head}, @garbanzo beans{1%can} (drained and rinsed), @red bell pepper{1} (sliced into thin 1-inch strips), @red onion{1/2} (chopped), @shredded Parmesan{1%cup}, and @salami{1/2%lb} (diced into 1/4-inch cubes) in a bowl. Toss with dressing and serve.
